{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "labs::uv_unitize", "icon": "uvunitize", "tags": "sidefxlabs,  model", "version": null, "namespace": "labs"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Labs UV Unitize"], "extent": [0, 20]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": [" Converts every primitive to 0-1 UVs  "], "extent": [119, 165]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Modifies the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["uv"]}, " attribute to fit in 0-1 space. It can do so in two ways. Each Face, or each UV Shell. In order to use the UV Shell mode, you need to provide input UV Shells with the specified UV attribute.\nUseful if you have a strip of polygons and want every face or shell to be perfectly unwrapped in 0-1 space."], "extent": [165, 483]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/uv_unitize_cube.png", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/uv_unitize_cube.png"}], "extent": [483, 520]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/uv_unitize.png", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/uv_unitize.png"}], "extent": [520, 552]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [552, 564], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Group"], "extent": [564, 575], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Isolates this operation to only this set of geometry"], "extent": [575, 636]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Mode"], "extent": [636, 646], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The mode at which the tool will fill the UVs in. Face will unwrap each primitive to fill 0-1 entirely, while Per UV Shell will measure the dimensions of each connected UV Shell and scale it to fit 0-1 as a whole."], "extent": [646, 867]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["UV Attribute"], "extent": [867, 885], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The attribute used for the operation. Note that this attribute name will be used to generate an attribute in Face mode, and will use incoming attributes with this name in UV Shell mode."], "extent": [885, 1083]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["Labs UV Unitize"], "summary": [" Converts every primitive to 0-1 UVs  "]}